
                           Short Stories  No.1
                                Document

Thank you for obtaining and using the Short Stories program. I hope that
you enjoy the first story to be published in this unique way. I am not
aware of any other company or individual publishing short stories
exclusively on computer disk, therefore I can claim my services to be
unique! If there is anyone else out there doing this then please let me
know. I have no doubt that now the idea has been realized there will be
many imitators, but just remember where you saw it first, right here with
Samsof Software.

The idea is really very simple. I have always wanted to be a book publisher
(I edited a magazine for over 2 years), and I have always been interested in
computers (particularly programming them), so rather than going to all the
hassle and expense of setting up a traditional publishing company, I decided
that the best thing to do was to put stories into a computer program rather
than onto paper, and publish them that way.

Did your parents and teachers always tell you that you should read rather
than going on your computer? Well now you can do both at the same time!


                          Installing the program

Once you have the program on your hard drive, before loading the program,
press the right amiga key and the 'e' key together. A command line will
appear. Just the following line into the command line:

              copy <program path>/fonts sys:fonts/ all

Change the <program path> to whichever path leads to the short story program
on your hard drive. For instance if your hard drive is called `Work:' and
the short story program is in adrawer called `story' then you would type
`Work:story' instead of <program path>.

When you have the correct command typed in, press the RETURN key or select
the OK gadget and the fonts will be copied to the fonts drawer in your boot
partition. If you have any problems with this procedure, please let me know.

When you completed this simple procedure, double click on the icon entitled
`ShortStory1' and the program should load up without any problems.


                            Using the Program

Once the program has loaded you will be presented with the first page which
tells you the name of the story and who wrote it. To advance a page press
the `+' key (either one of the two on the keyboard) and to go back a page
press the `-' key. You can select to go to a particular page by either
pressing the right mouse button and selecting a menu option or by pressing
the right amiga key and the page number together. So if you are reading page
3 and you want to go immediately to page 6 just press right Amiga and the
number 6 together. To go back to the title page, press right amiga and `S'
together.


                              DISCLAIMER

Samsof software supplies this product to you `as is'. This means that we
cannot be held responsible should the use of this software damage any part
of your computer by any means whatsoever. It is extremely unlikely that any
