                    Getting YOUR stories published

                           The small print

You are advised to read the following section through carefully before
submitting anything to Samsof, as, by  the action of submitting anything to
Samsof you demonstrate your acceptance of the following rules.

If you have written a story that you would like to see published then why
not send it to me. Subject to certain restrictions (nothing obscene or in
bad taste please!) I promise that I will consider all stories sent to me for
publication. If I decide not to publish your story for whatever reason, I
promise to let you know why the decision was taken. Please note, however,
that my decision is final.

If your story does get published, you will receive 20% of all the profit
made on it. That means that at current prices of £5.00 per story you will
receive £1 for every story sold! You will also get a FREE rigistered copy of
the program featuring your story. I can't be fairer than that, can I?

Please note that you receive a share of the profit on all programs sold. How
much you receive depends entirely on how many people buy your story. Samsof
cannot give any guarantees as to how much you will receive, or even whether
you will receive anything at all. In fact the ONLY guarantee that Samsof can
give you is that I will keep full and accurate records of all programs sold,
and that I WILL send you a FULL 20% of all money recieved (not including
money received for p+p as this is a cost, not profit).

So get those old stories out of the loft or knuckle down and write some
right now, after all what have got to lose? Even if you don't get any money
back for them (which is unikely as given a worldwide audience such as we
have, somebody is bound to be interested in whatever you write about), you
will still have the satisfaction of knowing that your stories were
published, and whatever happens, it will only cost you the price of a stamp
(or a local phone call in the case of E-mails). After that there is no
charge to you whatsoever. It is up to me to get your stories published and
earning money.

Please do not send me any stories that you have not personaly written or
that have been published elsewhere, particularly if they have been
copyrighted by someone else. Samsof must and will refuse to publish
copyrighted material, however should copyrighted material be inadvertantly
published then the submitter of the material and NOT Samsof will be
responsible for any consequences. All stories submitted to Samsof will
automatically be copyrighted to their authors by Samsof. By submitting a
story to Samsof the author automatically gives permission for Samsof to make
the story into a computer program, for commercial sale, subject to the
author receiving an agreed percentage of the profits that his story
generates (currently 20% however Samsof reserves the right to alter this
amount either up or down for new clients at any time and without warning,
however once an amount has been agreed upon, the agreed amount for
a particular story cannot be altered either by the author or by Samsof,
unless that story is re-released.


That's the end of the documents, I wish you every enjoyment with this and
other stories that you purchase from me.

    BYE BYE FOR NOW, I LOOK FORWAD TO RECIEVING YOUR REGISTRATION SOON!
